While deploying the code to server. It will ask for password. This is the password for bitbucket account from which code has been cloned from bitbucket.

You can find the username of bitbucket in server putty in project folder.

go to project folder 
list all hidden files by running command ls -a

you will find .git folder, change to .git folder by cd .git

now list all hidden files by ls -a
you will find config file, open that file using vi config

you will get to know the user of bitbucket linked to the current server

We can change this ownership of user(the user of bitbucket) by following steps from below url
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/22844806/how-to-change-my-git-username-in-terminal


